From: Drive on Chip <doc@altera.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Fix signal handler signature for GCC 15
Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [Altera example design]

signal() requires a handler of type void (*)(int). Update handlerStop
to accept the signal number.

---
 hps_safe_channel.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/hps_safe_channel.c b/hps_safe_channel.c
--- a/hps_safe_channel.c
+++ b/hps_safe_channel.c
@@ -108,8 +108,9 @@
  * Signals the threads to stop and clean pointers
  * this is triggered every ctrl+c
  */
-static void handlerStop()
+static void handlerStop(int sig)
 {
+    (void)sig;
     printf("received ctrl-c\n");
     *signalTerm = true;
     printf("Value terminal %d\n", *signalTerm);
